Guinda first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Guinda had a population of 245. The population density was {{convert|83.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Guinda was 166 (67.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 10 (4.1%) [[African Americans|African American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 20 (8.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 49 (20.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 67 persons (27.3%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Guinda CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0631540 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 108 households, out of which 39 (36.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 65 (60.2%) were married-couple households, 8 (7.4%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 27 (25.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 8 (7.4%) had a male householder with no partner present. 10 households (9.3%) were one person, and 4 (3.7%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.27.<ref name=DP1/> There were 87 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (80.6% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Guinda CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0631540 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 46 people (18.8%) under the age of 18, 9 people (3.7%) aged 18 to 24, 34 people (13.9%) aged 25 to 44, 87 people (35.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 69 people (28.2%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 54.8{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 94.4 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 126 housing units at an average density of {{convert|43.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 108 (85.7%) were occupied. Of these, 64 (59.3%) were owner-occupied, and 44 (40.7%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

